'''Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality''' ke Metropolitan Masepala gofeta diporofense [[Kapa Bohlabela]] kamoka [[Afrika Borwa]].
Setšhaba se 1,152,115 (2011 Palo ya batho), batho ba bulela [[Sethosa]] (54%), [[Afrikaans]] (29%) le [[Seisimane]] (14%). Municipal code ke NMA.

It is located on the shores of Algoa Bay in the [[Kapa Bohlabela|Eastern Cape]] province, and comprises the city of [[Port Elizabeth]], the nearby towns of [[Uitenhage]] and [[Despatch, Kapa Bohlabela|Despatch]], and the surrounding rural area.

The name "Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality" was chosen to honour former President [[Nelson Mandela]].

